<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="no"?>
<project xmlns="http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
         xsi:schemaLocation="http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0 http://maven.apache.org/maven-v4_0_0.xsd">

    <!--

    DEVELOPMENT ENVIRONTENT PREPARATION
    ===================================

    $ printf '\nprefix=${HOME}/.npm-packages\n' >> ${HOME}/.npmrc
    $ mkdir "${HOME}/.npm-packages"
    $ npm install -g protractor grunt bower grunt-contrib-compass
    Add to PATH: ${HOME}/.npm-packages/bin

    Install compass (word <minus> below replace by acutal sign '-'):

        # gem update <minus><minus>system
        # gem install compass

    on FreeBSD the package should be installed from system packages:

        # pkg install rubygem-compass

    The project is depended on the MS SQL server JDBC dirver.
    The driver is not available in the public Apache Maven repositories.
    It can be installed in a local Apache Maven cache by following command 
    (it assumes that current working dir is the top level project's
    directory - TurboInternational):

        $ mvn install:install-file -Dfile=../bits/libs/sqljdbc_4.2/enu/sqljdbc42.jar -DgroupId=com.microsoft.sqlserver -DartifactId=sqljdbc4 -Dversion=4.2 -Dpackaging=jar


    BUILD THE PROJECT
    ==================

    $ mvn -DskipTests -Dyo.test.skip=true -DbuildNumber=dev clean package

    of course you may skip -D options which disables run tests so the
    build will be tested.

    On FreeBSD a dependency on a PhantomJS is not available in NPM's
    repositories for this platform. So it should be installed from packages:

        # pkg install phantomjs


    RUN THE PROJECT
    ===============

    $ mvn clean package spring-boot:run -DskipTests -Dyo.test.skip=true -DbuildNumber=dev \
        -Dimages.originals=file:/var2/turbointernationa/metadata/product_images/originals/ \
        -Dimages.resized=file:/var2/turbointerantional/metadata/product_images/resized/

    -->

    <modelVersion>4.0.0</modelVersion>
    <groupId>com.turbointernational</groupId>
    <artifactId>metadata</artifactId>
    <version>${buildNumber}</version>
    <name>metadata</name>
    
    <parent>
        <groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
        <artifactId>spring-boot-starter-parent</artifactId>
        <!-- version>1.3.2.RELEASE</version -->
